          "ts": "1776257913.226679",
          "client_msg_id": "2bd469c9-5c5b-4a58-a52f-cdc6003bb098",
          "text": "Hello - *A new W-AR pricing sheet has been uploaded to the SOW folder and can be found here* - <https://disks.sharepoint.com/:x:/r/sites/GSESalesEngagement/Shared%20Documents/Versioned%20Templates%20%26%20Assets%20-%20WIP/Base%20Templates%20-%20WIP/Templates%20with%20New%20Title%20Page/W-AR%20Pricing%20Sheet%20(April%202026).xlsx?d=w2627d5c37056433cbf6fd130c544457f&amp;csf=1&amp;web=1&amp;e=2OYIdU|W-AR Pricing Sheet (April 2026).xlsx>.\n\nThe pricing sheet is meant to be used as a basis for quoting any well-architected review. Based on the recent work around W-ARs and the creation of the various templates, *we are averaging approximately 40 hours between all team members and meetings for delivery.* The work breaks down as follows:\n1. Initial reporting tool installation and review\n2. Workshop to review initial findings and perform further discovery on current architecture.\n3. Analysis and reporting\n4. Results review (Internal and Customer)\n<@UPWJZLCV7> has reviewed and approved the hours and stories in the pricing sheet.\n\n<@U015PLFUQET> <@U05UU07N5EW> - *Based on this pricing sheet the cost of a W-AR is now estimated at the following using the <https://aptum.atlassian.net/wiki/spaces/KAOS/pages/4985585665/Service+Delivery+Billable+Rates+Role+Definitions|current blended rate found here>.*\n• $11,000 (CAD) \n• $8,400 (USD) \n• £6,800 (GBP) \n• €7,600 (EUR)\nPlease let us know if we'll be using these new rates to quote to customers or if we'll be staying with the 'unofficial' $5K rate that's usually used.\n\nIf there are any questions about the pricing sheet, please reach out. Thank you - Barb",
          "team": "T024XGS0G",
